thou dost establish equity,
thou executest judgment and righteousness in Jacob.

99.6:
Moses and Aaron among his priests,
and Samuel among them that call upon his name;
they called upon the Lord, and he answered them.

99.9:
Exalt the Lord our God,
and worship at his holy hill;
for the Lord our God is holy.

100.3:
Know ye that the Lord he is God:
it is he that hath made us, and not we ourselves;
we are his people, and the sheep of his pasture.

102.2:
Hide not thy face from me in the day when I am in trouble;
incline thine ear unto me:
in the day when I call answer me speedily.

102.26:
They shall perish, but thou shalt endure:
yea, all of them shall wax old like a garment;
as a vesture shalt thou change them, and they shall be changed:

104.1:
Bless the Lord, O my soul. 
O Lord my God, thou art very great;
thou art clothed with honour and majesty.

104.14:
He causeth the grass to grow for the cattle,
and herb for the service of man:
that he may bring forth food out of the earth;

106.1:
Praise ye the Lord. 
O give thanks unto the Lord;
for he is good: for his mercy endureth for ever.

106.7:
Our fathers understood not thy wonders in Egypt;
they remembered not the multitude of thy mercies;
but provoked him at the sea, even at the Red sea.

106.43:
Many times did he deliver them;
but they provoked him with their counsel,
and were brought low for their iniquity.

107.3:
and gathered them out of the lands,
from the east, and from the west,
from the north, and from the south.

108.7:
God hath spoken in his holiness;
I will rejoice, I will divide Shechem,
and mete out the valley of Succoth.

108.8:
Gilead is mine; Manasseh is mine;
Ephraim also is the strength of mine head;
Judah is my lawgiver;

109.28:
Let them curse, but bless thou:
when they arise, let them be ashamed;
but let thy servant rejoice.

110.6:
He shall judge among the heathen,
he shall fill the places with the dead bodies;
he shall wound the heads over many countries.

112.9:
He hath dispersed, he hath given to the poor;
his righteousness endureth for ever;
his horn shall be exalted with honour.

112.10:
The wicked shall see it, and be grieved;
he shall gnash with his teeth, and melt away:
the desire of the wicked shall perish.

115.12:
The Lord hath been mindful of us:
he will bless us; he will bless the house of Israel;
he will bless the house of Aaron.

116.16:
O Lord, truly I am thy servant;
I am thy servant, and the son of thine handmaid:
thou hast loosed my bonds.

118.12:
They compassed me about like bees;
they are quenched as the fire of thorns:
for in the name of the Lord I will destroy them.

118.29:
O give thanks unto the Lord;
for he is good:
for his mercy endureth for ever.

130.7:
Let Israel hope in the Lord:
for with the Lord there is mercy,
and with him is plenteous redemption.

133.2:
It is like the precious ointment upon the head,
that ran down upon the beard, even Aaron’s beard:
that went down to the skirts of his garments;

